VERSION     = "1.5.1"
DESCRIPTION = "Cable AI Scalp v1.5.1 — patch release on top of v1.5's H1 over-extension band. (1) Fixes a pre-existing crash in the weekly/monthly Telegram report: reporting._setup_breakdown() now emits 'wins'/'losses' keys that telegram_templates._sec() requires (was raising KeyError: 'wins' on the By-Setup section, first surfaced by the first-Monday monthly report). (2) Relabels the H1-extension shadow log into three distinct cases — ext<0 'wrong side of H1 EMA (counter-trend)', 0<=ext<min 'whipsaw (on the line)', ext>max 'chase (extended)' — so negative readings are no longer mislabelled as whipsaws. No behaviour change to trading or to the band membership test; h1_ext_mode still ships 'off' (shadow)."
